          "date": "2022-07-27 15:15:06.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "subject": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix setting of target NID on rx",
        "message": "LU-16035 kfilnd: Fix setting of target NID on rx\n\nFor multi-rail configurations, on kfilnd_recv(), the message initiator\nmay not have the same NID as the kfilnd interface the message was sent\nfrom. To resolve this issue, when a new transaction request is\nreceived at the target, use the source NID from the packet as the\ntarget NID. This will lock in any follow up operations, such as RMA or\ntagged sends, to the kfilnd interface the original transaction request\narrived on.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nHPE-bug-id: LUS-9002\nSigned-off-by: Ian Ziemba <ian.ziemba@hpe.com>\nChange-Id: If28baf048583228cf781dea48aaadcbb884e0214\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
